'''Oswin Reagan Appollis''' also known as '''10111''' (born 25 August 2001) is a South African [[Association football|soccer player]] who currently plays as a [[Winger (association football)|winger]] or [[midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]] for [[South African Premiership]] club [[Orlando Pirates F.C.|Orlando Pirates]] and the [[South Africa national soccer team|South Africa national team]].

== Club career ==

=== Polokwane City ===
He featured for [[Polokwane City F.C.|Polokwane City]] during the 2023/24 and 2024/25 season in the [[South African Premier Division]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-08-01 |title=Polokwane City unwilling to budge on Oswin Appollis interest {{!}} soccer |url=https://www.sabcsport.com/soccer/news/polokwane-city-unwilling-to-budge-on-oswin-appollis-interest |access-date=2025-12-22 |website=SABC |language=en}}</ref>

=== Orlando Pirates ===
He joined [[Orlando Pirates F.C.|Orlando Pirates]] at the start of the 2025/26 season.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-12-07 |title=Appollis: I Made The Right Decision To Join Pirates |url=https://www.soccerladuma.co.za/psl/orlando-pirates/oswin-appollis-didn-t-hesitate-to-sign-for-orlando-pirates |access-date=2025-12-22 |website=Soccer Laduma |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-11-12 |title=Agent lifts the lid on how Orlando Pirates 'hijacked' Oswin Appollis, beating Kaizer Chiefs, Mamelodi Sundowns and Esperance to the Bafana Bafana star player's signature {{!}} Goal.com South Africa |url=https://www.goal.com/en-za/lists/agent-lifts-the-lid-on-how-orlando-pirates-hijacked-oswin-appollis-beating-kaizer-chiefs-mamelodi-sundowns-and-esperance-to-the-bafana-bafana-star-player-s-signature/bltf33ac829d1dff1ac |access-date=2025-12-22 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-ZA}}</ref>

== International career ==
Appollis scored his debut goal for South Africa against South Sudan in the 2025 Afcon qualifiers.

On 1 December 2025, Appollis was called up to the South Africa squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/afcon2025/news/totalenergies-afcon-morocco-2025-fever-rises-as-broos-become-first-coach-to-unveil-final-squad/|title=TotalEnergies AFCON Morocco 2025 fever rises as Broos become first coach to unveil final squad|publisher=[[Confederation of African Football]]|date=1 December 2025|access-date=12 December 2025}}</ref> He scored his fourth goal of 2025 against Angola at the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Mahlase |first=Eliot |date=2025-12-22 |title=Oswin Appollis: Four goals in five matches for Bafana |url=https://www.thesouthafrican.com/sport/soccer/bafana-bafana/oswin-appollis-four-goals-in-five-matches-for-bafana/ |access-date=2025-12-22 |website=The South African |language=en-ZA}}</ref>

